---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

<Layout title="Foundations | Identity Engineering">
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<section class="border-b border-white/10 px-6 py-20">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Foundations</div>
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-white md:text-6xl">Historical &amp; Conceptual Anchors</h1>
				<p class="mt-6 text-2xl text-white/70">The living reference layer that gives the Identity Stem its public weight and clarifies the engineering leap.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="px-6 py-16">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/80">
				<p>Foundations is the section where we keep the historical and conceptual anchors that ground Identity Engineering in rigorous precedent while making the differentiation unmistakable. Each page translates classical insight into the geometric primitives of the framework and shows where the engineering extension begins.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-16 bg-white/[0.015]">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-8 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Current Anchors</div>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<a href="/foundations/locke-personal-identity" class="block border-l border-white/15 pl-6 hover:border-white/40 transition-colors group">
						<div class="text-sm text-white/40">John Locke • 1689</div>
						<div class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white group-hover:text-white/90">Consciousness Continuity as Proto-Trajectory</div>
						<div class="mt-2 text-white/60">The forensic root of personal identity and the earliest sketch of the Identity Stem.</div>
					</a>
					<!-- Future anchors (Parfit, Ricöur, etc.) will appear here -->
				</div>
				<p class="mt-10 text-sm text-white/50">More anchors will be added as the field analysis deepens. Each new page follows the same geometric discipline.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
